  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response and assistance to Somali refugees</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">?	By providing all-weather shelter materials to 6,000 households, their physical protection and health will be improved, providing a sense of privacy and normality, hindering un-wanted intrusion and promoting a culture of good environmental management. The dome-shape shelters are made of a steel construction and tarpaulin; no wood will be used for shelter construction and the very fragile environment, including valuable incense trees, will be protected and good relations with the host community maintained. 
?	All newly arriving refugees are provided with two life-saving hot meals per day for 10 days at the transit centre until the set up of their own shelter and the distribution of kitchen sets and WFP food rations. This will prevent further deterioration of the already highly malnourished Somali refugees and prevent hypoglycaemia and the subsequent loss of life.</narrative>
  </description>
